article.description: Dimitrije Cabarkapa came off the bench to score 14 points and Ron Curry added 12 to lead James Madison to a 68-45 victory over Drexel on Thursday night.
article.headline: James Madison rolls past Drexel 68-45
article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. -- Dimitrije Cabarkapa came off the bench to score 14 points and Ron Curry added 12 to lead James Madison to a 68-45 victory over Drexel on Thursday night. The Dukes (15-5, 5-2) have won four straight and are in a four-way tie atop the Colonial Athletic Association. Kazembe Abif scored 15 points and Terrell Allen added 11 for Drexel (3-15, 1-6), which has lost three straight and seven of its last eight. The Dukes dominated the glass, 44-20, including 15-4 on the offensive end for a 17-3 edge in second-chance points while outscoring the Dragons 34-10 in the paint. The Dukes took an 11-point lead with 15 minutes left and remained in front by double figures, going up by 20 after 11-2 run capped by a jumper and 3-pointer by Cabarkapa with just under eight minutes left. Drexel shot just 22.7 percent in the first half when it trailed 28-18.
